and lived alongside for many years.

1366
01:04:55.805 --> 01:04:58.075
First, we need clear statutory duties

1367
01:04:58.855 --> 01:05:00.235
for more than 25 years.

1368
01:05:00.305 --> 01:05:03.075
Inquiry after inquiry has shown that when

1369
01:05:03.675 --> 01:05:06.715
responsibilities are vague, practice becomes inconsistent,

1370
01:05:06.935 --> 01:05:08.475
and people fall through the cracks.

1371
01:05:09.435 --> 01:05:12.715
National consistency isn't optional, it's foundational.

1372
01:05:13.735 --> 01:05:15.475
Second, continuity of care

1373
01:05:15.615 --> 01:05:18.325
and equity must be explicitly recognized.

1374
01:05:19.225 --> 01:05:22.365
We know who is disproportionately harmed when systems fail.

1375
01:05:23.285 --> 01:05:24.965
Disabled people, older adults,

1376
01:05:25.395 --> 01:05:27.285
medically dependent individuals.

1377
01:05:27.965 --> 01:05:31.365
Children, migrants, and others who rely on stable supports.

1378
01:05:31.775 --> 01:05:33.525
These are not each cases,

1379
01:05:34.275 --> 01:05:37.845
they are core populations whose needs must be built into the

1380
01:05:37.845 --> 01:05:39.765
system, not left a chance.

1381
01:05:41.095 --> 01:05:44.165
Third, we need structural cross-sector coordination.

1382
01:05:45.155 --> 01:05:48.445
Emergency management cannot function in isolation.

1383
01:05:49.025 --> 01:05:52.805
It relies on health, disability services, education,

1384
01:05:53.115 --> 01:05:55.605
welfare, lifeline, utilities,

1385
01:05:55.705 --> 01:05:59.165
and community organizations all being able to work together,

1386
01:06:00.025 --> 01:06:02.525
not just in principle, but in practice.

1387
01:06:03.425 --> 01:06:05.525
And this is where the bill must act

1388
01:06:05.625 --> 01:06:09.605
as both a statutory anchor and a statutory bridge.

1389
01:06:10.545 --> 01:06:13.685
The bill needs to anchor the emergency relevant duties

1390
01:06:13.795 --> 01:06:16.045
that already exist in other acts

1391
01:06:16.475 --> 01:06:19.725
because those duties are inevitably activated

1392
01:06:19.725 --> 01:06:21.245
during declared emergencies.

1393
01:06:21.545 --> 01:06:22.725
Sudden disasters

1394
01:06:23.105 --> 01:06:27.165
and prolonged cascading events at the same time.

1395
01:06:27.385 --> 01:06:30.565
It needs statutory bridges mechanisms

1396
01:06:30.565 --> 01:06:34.165
that allow emergency management organizations to reach out

1397
01:06:34.165 --> 01:06:37.325
and connect with your obligations held by other agencies.

1398
01:06:38.035 --> 01:06:41.165
Without these bridges, emos cannot lawfully

1399
01:06:41.225 --> 01:06:43.565
or consistently coordinate across sectors

1400
01:06:44.115 --> 01:06:46.645
even when the duties already exist elsewhere.

1401
01:06:47.815 --> 01:06:50.485
We've seen what happens when these elements are missing.

1402
01:06:51.145 --> 01:06:54.005
The North Island severe weather events inquiry showed

1403
01:06:54.005 --> 01:06:57.245
medically dependent people left without essential services.

1404
01:06:58.225 --> 01:07:01.645
The COVID-19 Royal Commission highlighted disproportionate

1405
01:07:01.675 --> 01:07:04.125
impacts on disabled people and older adults,

1406
01:07:05.675 --> 01:07:07.215
and the Canterbury Earthquakes,

1407
01:07:07.215 --> 01:07:10.855
and Pike River Royal Commissions identified deep failures in

1408
01:07:10.855 --> 01:07:12.175
cross-sector coordination.

1409
01:07:13.105 --> 01:07:17.135
These are long standing, well-documented systemic issues.

1410
01:07:17.885 --> 01:07:20.735
This bill is a rare opportunity to finally address them

1411
01:07:20.795 --> 01:07:22.495
by giving the system both the anchor

1412
01:07:22.915 --> 01:07:24.935
and the bridges it needs to function.

1413
01:07:26.035 --> 01:07:28.495
ENC closing. I support the intent of the bill,

1414
01:07:29.195 --> 01:07:32.295
but it strengths will depend on whether statutory duties,

1415
01:07:32.945 --> 01:07:35.095
continuity of care, equity,

1416
01:07:35.395 --> 01:07:37.895
and cross sector coordination are embedded

1417
01:07:37.895 --> 01:07:39.735
clearly and consistently.

1418
01:07:40.705 --> 01:07:42.485
We cannot afford another generation

1419
01:07:42.485 --> 01:07:44.205
of repeating the same failures.

